==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enucleate
<hw>E*nu"cle*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Enucleated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Enucleating</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>enucleatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>enucleare</ets> to enucleate;
<ets>e</ets> out + <ets>nucleus</ets> kernel.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
bring or peel out, as a kernel from its enveloping husks its enveloping
husks or shell.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>To remove without cutting (as a
tumor).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To bring to light; to make clear.</def>
<rj><au>Sclater (1654).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enucleation</ent>⟦br⟧
